                            <comment id="13529178" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Tue, 11 Dec 2012 18:07:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;TestSortedCopyOnWriteSet uses single thread in its tests.&lt;br/&gt;
We should enhance the test with multiple threads so that we can be confident the fix in this JIRA is effective.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13529273" author="ghelmling" created="Tue, 11 Dec 2012 19:52:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It also seems worth micro-benchmarking against ConcurrentSkipListSet and seeing if there is a big enough benefit here to make it worth maintaining our own implementation.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13529722" author="stack" created="Wed, 12 Dec 2012 07:50:00 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;It also seems worth micro-benchmarking against ConcurrentSkipListSet and seeing if there is a big enough benefit here to make it worth maintaining our own implementation.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Could we get rid of SortedCopyOnWriteSet Gary for CSLS?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Good stuff.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13530091" author="ghelmling" created="Wed, 12 Dec 2012 16:46:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;.bq Could we get rid of SortedCopyOnWriteSet Gary for CSLS?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That&apos;s the idea.  Given the lack of locking for CSLS, it may be just as low overhead for iteration and would actually be fully thread safe.  In which case, let&apos;s dump SortedCopyOnWriteSet if it doesn&apos;t buy us anything.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13530230" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Wed, 12 Dec 2012 19:22:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 on dropping SortedCopyOnWriteSet&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
